489
00:15:04,350 --> 00:15:05,000
I do.

490
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:05,640
You do?

491
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,280
Yes,

492
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:06,790
I do.

493
00:15:06,790 --> 00:15:07,570
I really like dogs.

494
00:15:08,710 --> 00:15:09,910
You may like my dog.

495
00:15:10,710 --> 00:15:11,520
It's cute.

496
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,640
Guess what my dog's name is.

497
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:17,910
Wangcai.

498
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:19,880
It's close.

499
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:22,000
Puppy name?

500
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:23,710
It's a common name.

501
00:15:23,710 --> 00:15:24,320
Zhaocai.

502
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,840
His guess Wangcai is close.

503
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:31,030
Wangwang.

504
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,440
Wangwang?

505
00:15:33,230 --> 00:15:34,320
Yeah, it's called Wangwang.

506
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:39,540
(Looking around)

507
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:41,640
I'm so hungry.

508
00:15:43,470 --> 00:15:44,840
When can we have dinner?

509
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,580
I thought this is the only kitchen.

510
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:50,030
So there's another kitchen, right?

511
00:15:50,550 --> 00:15:52,320
I really think it's them doing it.

512
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,200
It's so slow.

513
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:54,840
I can imagine

514
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,030
how they...

515
00:15:56,670 --> 00:15:57,840
We'll definitely have to guess

516
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,470
who made what.

517
00:15:59,470 --> 00:16:00,400
So those few dishes are

518
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:01,670
their ticket to enter the island.

519
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,230
Probably.

520
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:05,910
Have you finished?

521
00:16:05,910 --> 00:16:06,230
I have.

522
00:16:06,230 --> 00:16:07,150
Finished long ago.

523
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:07,880
Waiting for you.

524
00:16:08,230 --> 00:16:09,640
I want to give you a hand.

525
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:11,150
Hurry up and we can eat.

526
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:12,550
Fellow islanders.

527
00:16:13,470 --> 00:16:16,000
Please finish the work at hand asap.

528
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,710
Bring the meals you have prepared,

529
00:16:17,710 --> 00:16:18,960
head to Balance Island,

530
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:20,440
and meet with other islanders.

531
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,910
What?

532
00:16:24,230 --> 00:16:25,670
I thought it was just for us to eat.

533
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:26,340
Wait a sec.

534
00:16:26,340 --> 00:16:27,230
Let me season the dish.

535
00:16:27,230 --> 00:16:27,780
(Making up)

536
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,340
(Not finished)
Make a baby cabbage.

537
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:31,030
I'm also short of one dish.

538
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,590
The fire is too strong.

539
00:16:33,110 --> 00:16:34,200
It's done.

540
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,000
Let's move.

541
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:37,520
Have we finally landed on the island?

542
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,640
This island is really nice.

543
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,790
It has a great vibe.

544
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,030
Is this the place?

545
00:16:44,030 --> 00:16:45,000
It should be.

546
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,230
I think I saw them.

547
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:48,280
There are already people here.

548
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,790
Hello.

549
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:53,540
(Finally, you're here.)

550
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:54,670
They're here.

551
00:16:57,760 --> 00:16:59,030
Hello.

552
00:17:00,030 --> 00:17:03,440
Thank you for your hard work.

553
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:09,400
Can you cook?

554
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,950
I can cook a little.

555
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:12,640
Then take a look.

556
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,710
Does it need

557
00:17:13,710 --> 00:17:14,710
some adjustment?

558
00:17:14,710 --> 00:17:16,560
Should we add a little less hot water?

559
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:18,800
We should add some hot water.

560
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:20,560
I'll go boil some hot water.

561
00:17:22,830 --> 00:17:23,640
One bottle should...

562
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:26,960
I'll boil some

563
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:27,590
and add it in.

564
00:17:27,590 --> 00:17:28,470
It should be enough.

565
00:17:28,470 --> 00:17:29,190
Is it enough?

566
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:30,640
It should be enough.

567
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:31,800
I'm not sure.

568
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:36,190
How many dishes is each of you
responsible for?

569
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:38,000
Two to three?

570
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,920
So you all know how to cook?

571
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:41,310
Some of us don't.

572
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:42,590
I'm very good at it.

573
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:43,500
They are more skilled.

574
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,040
He's the best.

575
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:44,400
No.

576
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:44,950
He's the best.

577
00:17:44,950 --> 00:17:45,680
No.

578
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:48,190
And Evan is also super good at cooking.

579
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:49,160
The one in green clothes.

580
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:51,230
I want to smell it.

581
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:52,640
Can you all handle raw food?

582
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:52,950
I can't.

583
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:54,000
You don't or...?

584
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,070
I can't eat it.

585
00:17:55,310 --> 00:17:55,950
What about

586
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:56,710
the grilled kind?

587
00:17:56,710 --> 00:17:57,950
I can't eat seafood.

588
00:17:57,950 --> 00:17:59,520
It's that all seafood is not okay.

589
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:00,760
So it's not a matter of raw food

590
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:01,230
but seafood.

591
00:18:01,230 --> 00:18:01,640
Right.

592
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,160
Yes.

593
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:05,590
I want to ask who cooked this.

594
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:07,710
Scrambled eggs?

595
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:10,640
Me, the worst at cooking.

596
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:11,920
